<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><song><lyrics>[V1]
 Are you ready for a miracle
 As ready as I can be
 Are you ready for a miracle
 The spirit will set you free
 Are you ready, ready, ready, ready
 Are you ready, are you ready for a miracle

[V2]
 Jesus went unto the well
 And made the water wine
 Raised the captives from the dead
 Restored the sight unto the blind
 Jesus was from Galilee
 He walked across the sea
 He said Greater things you shall do
 He gave the power to you and me

[V3]
 Are you ready for a miracle...

[V4]
 Jesus help the lame to walk
 He fought the Devil back
 Healed the leper, fed five thousand
 With just one command
 Said, He who has ears, let him hear,
 He told the multitudes
 And blessed be the pure of heart
 for they shall see the truth

[V5]
 Are you ready for a miracle...

[V6]
 Blessed be the ones who mourn for
 They shall find their peace
 Blessed be the ones who thirst
 And blessed be the meek
 Are you ready, ready
 Are you ready, ready
 Blessed be the innocent
 For they shall all be free
 Blessed be the miracle
 That's waiting for you and me
 Are you ready, ready
 Are you ready, ready

[V7]
 Are you ready for a miracle...

[V8]
 Are you ready?
 Are you ready?

[V9]
 Are you ready for a miracle...

[V10]
 Are you ready for a miracle?</lyrics>
<title>Ready for a miracle</title>
<hymn_number>1917</hymn_number>
<author>Livingospel</author>
</song>